# 1. Host Discovery

## Objective
Identify live hosts within the target network.

## Command

```bash
nmap -sn <TARGET-IP>
```

## Output File

```bash
nmap -sn <TARGET-IP> -oN raw-output/host-discovery.txt
```

## Explanation

- `-sn` : Performs host discovery only.
- Skips port scanning.
- Determines whether the host is alive.

